column5: I'd never leave. I've grown gills now.

If I tried that I'd get a cramp in my fat roll and would have to call for help. 

Not a pretty picture.
No no no. Not that sweet baby!!

Dogs should get a healthy amount of vegetables in their diet but they are also meat eaters. If she was refusing her previous food it could have been due to an allergy. Believe it or not, dogs tend to have allergies to a lot of additives in their food. 

Raw diet is a great way to go and you can always find a supplier with nutritional information and suggestions for each breeds specific needs :)
I'm sorry that it's causing you issues but that is still the coolest eye I have ever seen!!!
This is one of the coolest things I have ever seen
Holy shit!! Why the hell do I just fly across the room when I try that?!?!
Wow!? So vibrant! What a beautiful snake.

I am so sorry that you had to suffer at the hands of the one person who should be your protector. 

With that said, I don't believe you were in the wrong. You need to do anything you have to on order for your own health, mental and physical. 

She sounds like a very toxic person and you don't need that in your life when you're trying to heal. 

Good luck in the future. I hope you have love and peace in your journey.
I'd have accidently pushed the little darling off his chair.

I don't know how to answer that question with a small sentence.

What didn't happen? 

I was born. Abused, raped, beaten, had a shitty life. 

Got physical disabilities, mental disabilities and all the baggage that comes with it. 

I hate everything about me and my life and look forward to nothing. 

I'm alone, lonely, depressed, a burden and in the way. 

I just want it all to end.
